aml (Andri's Main Loop)

AML is a portable and simple event loop library for C. It provides the
essential building blocks for asynchronous programming including file
descriptor event handlers, timers, tickers, signal handlers, idle dispatch
callbacks, and a thread pool. The library is designed with portability,
utility, and simplicity in mind, and offers interoperability with other
event loops.

Features:
- File descriptor event handlers
- Timers
- Tickers
- Signal handlers
- Idle dispatch callbacks
- Thread pool
- Interoperability with other event loops

Homepage: https://github.com/any1/aml
